72. Write the PHP program to implement the following session functions.
(i)session_register() (ii) session_unset() (iii) session_destroy()

ANSWER
<?php
session_start();  // Start the session

// (i) Instead of session_register(), assign session variables directly
$_SESSION['username'] = "JohnDoe";
$_SESSION['email'] = "john@example.com";
echo "<h3>Session variables after registration:</h3>";
print_r($_SESSION);

// (ii) session_unset() - frees all session variables
session_unset();
echo "<h3>Session variables after session_unset():</h3>";
print_r($_SESSION); // Should be empty array
// Reassign a session variable for demo
$_SESSION['username'] = "JohnDoe";

// (iii) session_destroy() - destroys the session data on the server
session_destroy();
echo "<h3>Session after session_destroy():</h3>";
if (empty($_SESSION)) {
    echo "Session variables are cleared.";
} else {
    print_r($_SESSION);
}
?>

OUTPUT
Session variables after registration:
Array ( [username] => JohnDoe [email] => john@example.com )
Session variables after session_unset():
Array ( )
Session after session_destroy():
Array ( [username] => JohnDoe )

